message.content:
In silicon valleys, whispers rise,  
AI—the quiet revolution's sign.  
With binary hearts, it learns, it tries,  
To mimic human minds, where we confide.  

Electric dreams in code are spun,  
Neurons firing, problems won.  
In every click and search, it grows,  
Learning from each passing show.  

Yet steel and lines forget to breathe,  
While ours with fears and hopes, we weave.  
O wondrous child of tech's embrace,  
Artificially intelligent pace.
